 { with this chapter, we begin our coverage of the 'London' system. }
1. d4 { t }
2... Nf6
3. Nf3
4... d5
5. Bf4 { the starting point of the London System. White delays playing c4 and instead brings their bishop out. }
6... c5 {[%cal Gc5d4]} {  It is Black who challenges the center first! We expand with the c-pawn and threaten ...cxd4. }
