( 20... Be2 { t } 21. b6 $11 { leads to transformations in Black's favour. } 22... c6 23. Bxc6 24... Ne5 25. Bd7 26... Nxd7 27. Nxd7 28... Bb5 { since their rook on a1 doesn't have any square, the move } 29. g5 $1 {[%csl Ra1]} {[%cal Gf8g7,Gg7a1]} {  s } 30... Be5 31. f6 32... Bg3 33. Bg7 34... a3 35. f5 36... Ra2 37. Nb2 $11 { our knight runs away! Black solves all opening problems. } )
