( 10... Bd3 { t } 11. c5 { we are able to challenge the center. } 12... dxc5 13. Nc6 14... Nf3 ( 15. Na4 { t } 16... e5 {[%cal Rf6d7,Rd7c5]} {  we can play ...Nd7-Nc5 next. } ) 15. Bg4 16... Qd2 17. Bxf3 18... gxf3 19. e5 20... Bg3 21. Bxc5 $11 { Black keeps an easier game due to their center. } )
